    <node id="University of the Witwatersrand">
      <data key="d0">University of the Witwatersrand</data>
      <data key="d1">organization</data>
      <data key="d2">The University of the Witwatersrand is a prominent institution in South Africa that plays a significant role in research and academia. It is an institution where several authors, including Tshilidzi Marwala and Bodie Crossingham, are affiliated, as well as Vukosi N. Marivate, Fulufhelo V. Nelwamodo, and others. The university is particularly known for its work on genetic algorithms and rough set theory, with research conducted by affiliated authors. This institution serves as a school where these researchers and authors are able to conduct their studies and contribute to the academic community in South Africa.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-09515a99517089fa5af4576ca920495b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ec7bd9a39e04662c8ff1bc365bc4d621&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ce3fc4c8e86937d2da228e79428b766d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1fbb47252f8fa1089bfb224fbf2dd1c6&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-089b0c6bd4bd0479f72dcbbef975a69e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-33898e4a09fbbd847fa5a95728b135f8&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-739dd79489662ba784564dce7db2c583&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3868fdfd614e68dbdcdec9c13eb0df71</data>
