      <data key="d2">**World Athletics Championship**

The World Athletics Championship is a prominent global sports competition that brings together top athletes from around the world to showcase their skills in various track and field events. The championship has been held at different locations over the years, with one notable host city being Tokyo.

This international event features athletes competing in a range of disciplines, including sprinting, distance running, hurdling, relay racing, and throwing events like shot put and javelin throw. The World Athletics Championship is governed by World Athletics, which oversees all aspects of the competition to ensure fairness and adherence to established rules.

Tokyo has been identified as one of the host cities for the championship, showcasing the global reach of this prestigious event. The championship's focus on track and field events highlights its importance in promoting athletic excellence worldwide.

